You should use the iterator you've got from dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator() to get the children in each loop iteration.
Here's how you can do it:
for (Iterator<DataSnapshot> it = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator(); it.hasNext(); ) {
    i = i + 1;
    names.add(it.next().getValue(String.class));
}

This way, you're using the same iterator to get all the children of the snapshot.

